    "work_description": "Approval of a 22¿(w) x 49¿(l) x 41¿(h) enclosure to house a reduced pressure backflow assembly (RPBA) device and a new replacement cast concrete water fountain along the southern perimeter of Pettygrove Park, per the approved site plans, Exhibits C-1 through C-6, signed and dated 5/29/25, subject to the following conditions: A.As part of the building permit application submittal, the following development-related conditions (B through D) must be noted on each of the four required site plans or included as a sheet in the numbered set of plans. The sheet on which this information appears must be labeled \"ZONING COMPLIANCE PAGE- Case File LU 25-026358 HR.\" All requirements must be graphically represented on the site plan, landscape, or other required plan and must be labeled \"REQUIRED.\" B.At the time of building permit submittal, a signed Certificate of Compliance form (https://www.portland.gov/ppd/documents/design-and-historic-resource-review-approvals-certificate-compliance) must be submitted to ensure the permit plans comply with the Design/Historic Resource Review decision and approved exhibits. C.At time of permit, specifications must be provided to demonstrate the replacement concrete within the pedestrian walkways match to the existing original concrete in color, mix, aggregate (count, color and size), texture, panel size, and scoring. In addition, the permit plans must demonstrate full concrete panels are replaced (not portions). D. No field changes allowed.",
